category: TIPS FROM THE ANCIENTS
category comment: 

clue: The moral of his town & country mice fable is that a simple, peaceful life is better than riches with unease

response: Aesop

clue: In his "Analects", this Asian thinker was among those who suggested not to do to others what you don't want done to you

response: Confucius

clue: Simple machine of which Archimedes said that with the right place to stand he could move the world

response: a lever

clue: Completes the Hippocratic injunction "to help, or at least, to do..."

response: no harm

clue: In his "Meditations" this stoic Roman emperor wrote, "Every instant of time is a pinprick of eternity"

response: Marcus Aurelius

